\newlabel{fig:recovery_heatmap}{{5}{24}{The recovery surface of Table~\ref {tab:surface} as a heatmap (brighter $=$ better recovery). At clean labels ($q=0$) recovery is near-perfect from $f\ge 30$; noise darkens the surface, and the damage is concentrated at small $f$ and worst for admissible/complete --- but every semantics recovers to the bright band as $f$ grows}{figure.5}{}}
