\newlabel{fig:recovery_curves}{{6}{25}{The same surface as recovery-vs-sample-size curves, one line per semantics. The ``noise is bought back by data'' effect (E1.2) is the upward slope in the $q=0.2$ panel: recovery rises from $0.48$--$0.74$ at $f=10$ to $0.94$--$0.96$ at $f=80$, with no plateau below clean performance}{figure.6}{}}
