\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {8}{\ignorespaces Recovery versus label noise at a fixed, fully-complete sample size ($f=20$, balanced arm), with full labels ($p=1.0$, left) and half labels ($p=0.5$, right). Error bars are $95\%$ confidence intervals over the five cross-validation folds (clipped to the valid MCC range). Partial labels turn a gentle, low-variance noise response into a steep, high-variance one --- the same noise is far more damaging when labels are also incomplete.}}{28}{figure.8}\protected@file@percent }
